Authentication

authentication : verifying identity : 401
authorization  : verifying permissions : 403

stateful : session using cookie
stateless : token using JWT / OAuth / other

stateful : session is stored server-side in ( memory, cache (Redis, Memcached) or DB (postgress or MongoDB) )

Cookies:
	Cookie is a header like Authorization or Content-Type 
	Server send header Set-Cookie and browser send header Cookie
	used in session management, tracking of User
	flags: 
		HttpOnly (no js access to cookie) 
		Secure ( https only )
		SameSite ( can be only sent from the same domain, no CORS sharing )
	CSRF:
	
